# Execution Delegation Safety Protocol

When delegating implementation tasks to multiple subagents in chat runtime, prevent edit collisions.

## 1) Build A Work Partition Before Delegating

- Split by **owned file sets**, not by vague themes.
- Assign each subagent exclusive ownership of concrete paths.
- Keep ownership disjoint whenever possible.

## 2) Shared File Rule

- If a shared/core file must change, assign it to exactly one **integrator** subagent.
- Other subagents must not edit integrator-owned files.

## 3) Delegation Contract (must be explicit)

Every subagent brief must include:

- objective
- owned files
- forbidden files (owned by others)
- required outputs (code/tests/docs)

## 4) Merge Strategy

- Run subagents in parallel only for disjoint ownership.
- If ownership overlaps, run in phases (serial handoff), not parallel.
- Integrator applies final cross-cutting edits after other streams finish.

## 5) Verification Gate

Before final response:

- confirm no two subagents edited the same file in the same phase
- run tests/lints relevant to changed files
- summarize per-stream ownership and final integrated result
